// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_Rog_SL6-7_Task_04 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - Duffy 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P4250149799" "Captain Duffy's True Identity"
// DetailString :
"P3741652198" "You found a surprising bit of information in a computer belonging to one Captain Duffy. It turns out the good captain is actually a sleeper agent for the 5th Column, hiding within the Rogue Isles Police until his proper orders come in to activate."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - Totting 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P1784646363" "Captain Totting's Fighting Ring"
// DetailString :
"P1571503784" "You found some information regarding a fighting ring Captain Totting runs in the basement of his house in Mercy City. It isn't fighting involving animals - it's fighting between the Infected on Mercy and the homeless! He keeps a small group of them in his basement, barely fed, using them as sport in the island. He pulls in a good amount of cash, as well, running this operation."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - Lopez 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P2615258309" "Captain Lopez's Snake Worshipping"
// DetailString :
"P299789117" "Mistress Julia had found some interesting photos of Captain Lopez. It seems like Lopez joined one of the snake cults to worship their god. However he isn't in the cult with other people - he's in it with other snakes! He's been a member for quite some time, considering how old some of these photos are."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P4005692126" "It's known to everyone in the Rogue Isles that the majority of the Rogue Isles Police are corrupt - one trip to Mercy to see one of their infamous 'Infected Fighting Rings' will tell you that much. The fact that this convention is happening in St. Martial, one of the richest parts of the Isles, means someone else is backing them - either Arachnos, or one of the other several groups who have the police in their pockets. <br><br> This convention will mean the RIP will start getting some more press soon - the reporter Amanda Vines would probably kill to have some juicy information on them to release. <br><br> Given that she isn't one to kill, there's always the next best thing - being paid to blackmail the higher ups in the RIP."
// AcceptString :
"P3224975124" "Sneak into the RIP offices to find blackmail information."
// SendOffString :
"P556591336" "One of the main RIP offices is in St. Martial. It would explain why so many of the officers can be found gambling instead of actually doing their job."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P1975414929" "Find Blackmail Information!"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P3852374642" "You'll have to gauge how much this information should go for - once you find it."
// TaskTitle :
"P4253476770" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>The RIP Wants YOU!</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color Yellow><i>Rogue Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P3775473640" "The smell of heavy perfume fills the air. It seems like the Carnival of Shadows had the same idea you did. They're getting away with that precious information!"
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P501238322" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>The RIP Wants YOU!</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color Yellow><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>The people from WSPDR were more than excited when you contacted them regarding the information you found. The deal was simple to make - they had a surprising amount of money to send your way for what you found. They should be airing it all in a weekly special called, 'RIP - Secrets Unveiled!'"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - Computer 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
