// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_Rog_SL6-7_Task_06 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - Rikti 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P3718477844" "Rikti Investigation"
// DetailString :
"P4018570176" "You went into the destroyed Arachnos base assuming that the worst was over. But as luck would have it, the Rikti have teleported in a scouting team. They seem to be searching for something - most likely the same thing you're looking for. Great."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - ArachnosCloning 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P2119269800" "Arachnos Cloning Operation"
// DetailString :
"P382502293" "The Arachnos computer showed you exactly what you were looking for - what they were doing here. <br><br> Arachnos was working on a mass cloning device within these labs. They planned to take the best operatives from the Bane Spiders, Fortunatas, and Destined Ones, and use them to create a super powerful army. Some Rikti DNA was also involved - specifically in strengthening the mental network that the Bane Spiders already have. <br><br> Looks like the Rikti came here to take that technology for themselves! If they get their hands on this, it could easily lead to a third Rikti War!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P4238556781" "This might be the most chaotic battle you've heard about in quite some time - and you've heard/seen your fair share of chaotic battles. Whatever caused Longbow to go in there with their full might must have been pretty impressive. Though judging by the chaos, it's likely that Longbow's purpose for going in there will be lost for some time. <br><br> Sounds like the perfect chance for someone like you to go in there once the dust is settled to see what exactly the big fuss was about - most importantly before someone else does!"
// AcceptString :
"P4247496187" "Wait for the battle to subside then investigate the source of it!"
// SendOffString :
"P3539304528" "You keep the transmission on, waiting to hear for the battle to die down. Sure enough, you hear the retreats being sounded by all the various groups - Longbow pulling out to treat everyone's wounds, Arachnos abandoning the base, the 5th Column chasing after the retreating Council...the Carnies getting bored and leaving.  The Devouring Earth began attacking all of the activists outside, causing the PPD to chase the monsters out. Now is the perfect time for you to get in there and see what exactly the big deal was."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P2229244458" "Investigate the Arachnos Base!"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P3638268662" "Hopefully you won't find any resistance - who else could possibly be left?"
// TaskTitle :
"P2493201567" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Sounds of Utter Chaos</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color Yellow><i>Rogue Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P2495285169" "The base is still covered in flames - which is fine, as long as what you're looking for is still intact, somewhere."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P1884569178" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Sounds of Utter Chaos</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color Yellow><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>There wasn't any real profit to be had by that expedition, but you did ensure the safety of the world by stopping the Rikti from obtaining that device. That will at least make future deals smoother - things tend to get lost in translation when a Rikti dropship is bombing the building you're doing business in."
// Script Variable INACTIVE_DIALOG_MINION1 :
"P3903259396" "Search base: Arachnos device"
// Script Variable ATTACK_DIALOG_MINION1 :
"P465096074" "{HeroName}: Interesting."
// Script Variable INACTIVE_DIALOG_MINION2 :
"P3874139722" "Memo: thank Arachnos for turning tide."
// Script Variable ATTACK_DIALOG_MINION2 :
"P2838615511" "Destroy: {HeroName}."

